
DRAW.   Choose an ink well (finger/CONTROL keys), then draw with the  LEFT  and
erase with the RIGHT mouse button. For text,  click on TEXT and the finger will
will change to a cross.    Press the LEFT button for a cursor and start typing.
Press [RETURN]  and the cross will reappear.   Click on TEXT or press the RIGHT
button  to return to DRAW mode but the  LEFT button will give you  text  again.
Move  finger or cross to the small black square to finish.  You now  have  four
options.
    (1)Type in a title and press [RETURN]. The drawing will be saved.
    (2)Press '/' if the drawing already has a title. The drawing will be saved.
    (3)Press [RETURN] and return to the directory. The drawing is not saved.
    (4)Press the space bar to return to text mode.
Animation  requires a series of pictures,  numbered from 1 to 9  and A up to I.
To PAUSE,  press ALTERNATE;  to stop press LEFT SHIFT or  ALTERNATE/LEFT SHIFT.
You will now be in DRAW mode.  RS,  AltRS and AltLS all restart animation.   RS
and AltRs save the amended picture but AltLS does not.
     To COPY a section press CONTROL/LEFT SHIFT or click on DRAW. A cross  will
appear. Put it in the bottom right corner of the section  and drag it up and to
the  left.  Release the button when the frame covers the section  and press  it
again  to record or "TAKE" the section.  "TAKE" -> "COPY". Press the right but-
ton to cancel.
     Press ALTERNATE instead of the LEFT mouse button for other options:-
ROTATE, ZOOM, POLYGON, CIRCLE, and STAR.               Now press the SPACE BAR.
